<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-292-088  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 292 088.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 22 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technology stocks: midweek quarterly results, Wed Mar 21.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Verhelst, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryReportsCompaniesProfit.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>TECHNOLOGY STOCKS: Midweek Quarterly Results, Wed Mar 21 NEW YORK, NEW YORK,U.S.A, 1990 MAR 21 (NB) -- Technology stocks retreated in the beginning ofthis week.andP;  Among issues reporting financial results:andM;[] Canadian GEAC Computer Corp. reports quarterly earnings of $317,000 forthe third quarter ending January 31, 1990 while for the first nine months ofthe year, earnings reached $2.59 million.andP;  Revenues stood at $17.077 and$52.248 million respectively.andP;  Founded in 1971, GEAC is Canada's largestcomputer software and hardware vendor.andM;[] 3COM earned $6.7 million during the third quarter which ended February 20,1990 on revenues of $107.3 million.andP;  For the nine months, sales slighlyexceeded the $302 million mark while profits stood at $13.2 million, downfrom last year's $26.1 million.andP;  3Com manufactures computer networkingsystems and associated equipment and competes with companies such as Novell.andM;[] Summagraphics reported net income of $1.7 million in the third quarterending February 28, 1990 with sales reaching $11.57 million, representing a4.3 percent increase over last year's results for the similar period.andP;  Forthe nine month period, the company reported sales of $33.667 million andearnings of $5.27 million.andP;  Summagraphics produces digitized systems and micefor personal computers.andM;[] Adobe Systems reports net income of $10.1 million for the first quarterending March 2, 1990.andP;  Revenues for the period were $37.181 million, up 46percent from the same period in the prior year.andP;  Apple Computer was thecompany largest customer representing more than 23 percent of its sales whileall the 23 other OEM customers paid a $24.226 million royalty to Adobe.andO;Adobe is the developer and holds copyrights and patents to the Postscriptfonts used widely in the high-end personal computer market.andM;(John Verhelst/19900321)</TEXT></DOC>